						<summary>

						<p>Nandi pillar (east face) in the Vīśvēvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1210, Māgha ba. 8,</hi> but the cyclic year is not mentioned it may be assigned to 1288 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to record a gift of land for two lamps, one in the shrine of Gaṇēśvara and the second in the temple of Komarēśvara by an individual (name lost).</p>						

						</summary>
